                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="346024" author="JIRAUSER18408" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2022 12:54:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks the issue can be closed.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="344802" author="JIRAUSER18408" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2022 14:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you found it, it is on the MGS server.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="344788" author="adilger" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2022 13:23:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you don&apos;t have any &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lod.&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; parameters it is likely because you are not running this on the MDS, or the filesystem is not mounted, or using a Lustre version that does not support DoM (no version information is given in the ticket). This is a parameter on the MDS and should be set there.  If setting it permanently, then use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param -P lod.&amp;#42;MDT0000&amp;#42;.dom_stripesize=NNNN&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on the MGS (if separate from the MDS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mds# lctl get_param lod.*.dom_stripesize
lod.myth-MDT0000-mdtlov.dom_stripesize=1048576
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
